{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/78829", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/78829/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/78829/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/78829/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/78829", "id": 738203142, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU3MzgyMDMxNDI=", "number": 78829, "title": "macro_rules expansion of `:expr` depends on content (can expand to a statement)", "user": {"login": "thepowersgang", "id": 955596, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjk1NTU5Ng==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/955596?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang", "html_url": "https://github.com/thepowersgang", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thepowersgang/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2020-11-07T08:56:30Z", "updated_at": "2020-11-08T00:45:25Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The following code compiles, despite the macro specifing `$e` to be an expression (and not a statement).\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nmacro_rules! test_mac {\r\n\t// It seems that :expr is parsed as a statement if it starts one?\r\n\t(@one $e:expr) => {{\r\n\t\t$e\r\n\t\t0\r\n\t\t}};\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n\tlet _ = test_mac!(@one if false {} );\t//< Allowed\r\n\t//let _ = test_mac!(@one ());\t//< Errors\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt appears that the contents of an interpolated expression (`:expr` capture) changes how the rest of the expanded macro is parsed.\r\n\r\nNot sure if this is a big issue, but is something I noticed while implementing mrustc (see `rustc-1.39.0-src\\vendor\\indexmap\\src\\map.rs:342`) for this behaviour in the wild.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`: \r\n```\r\nrustc 1.47.0 (18bf6b4f0 2020-10-07)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: 18bf6b4f01a6feaf7259ba7cdae58031af1b7b39\r\ncommit-date: 2020-10-07\r\nhost: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc\r\nrelease: 1.47.0\r\nLLVM version: 11.0\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/78829/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/78829/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}